100 Days of DevOps  ‚Äî Day 28(28/100)

üí≠ Small daily habits create big lifetime changes.
üî• Stay consistent


1Ô∏è‚É£ Why do we use SonarQube?
SonarQube is used to automatically check code quality.
 It detects bugs, security issues, and bad coding practices early.

2Ô∏è‚É£ What are Bugs in SonarQube?
Bugs are coding errors that can cause the application to fail or behave wrongly.
 Example: null pointer exception, wrong logic, infinite loop.
3Ô∏è‚É£ What are Vulnerabilities?
Vulnerabilities are security weaknesses in the code.
 Attackers can exploit them to access data or damage the system.

4Ô∏è‚É£ What is Code Smell?
Code smell means poor-quality code that works but is hard to maintain.
 It increases technical debt and future bugs.

5Ô∏è‚É£ What is Code Duplication?
Code duplication means same code repeated in multiple places.
 It makes changes harder and increases the chance of errors.

6Ô∏è‚É£ What is Code Coverage?
Code coverage shows how much code is tested using automated tests.
 Higher coverage means better-tested and more reliable code.
7Ô∏è‚É£ What is Security Rating?
Security rating shows how secure the application code is.
 It is graded from A (best) to E (worst).

8Ô∏è‚É£ What is Maintainability Rating?
Maintainability rating shows how easy the code is to modify or fix.
 Clean and simple code gets a better rating.

9Ô∏è‚É£ What is Technical Debt?
Technical debt is extra work needed later due to poor coding now.
 More debt means more maintenance effort in the future.

üîü What is Quality Gate?
Quality Gate is a set of conditions the code must pass.
 If it fails, build or deployment can be stopped.


============================


Bugs = Errors in code that cause wrong behavior or crashes

Vulnerabilities = Security weaknesses that attackers can exploit

Code Smell = Poor design that makes code hard to maintain

Code Duplication = Same logic written in multiple places

Code Coverage = Amount of code executed by automated tests

Security Rating = Indicator of how secure the application is

Maintainability Rating = Indicator of how easy the code is to modify

Technical Debt = Future effort caused by poor coding decisions

Quality Gate = Conditions that code must meet to be accepted

Static Code Analysis = Code inspection without running the program
